Japan tops all countries by promising to donate US$500 million;
followed by the United States with US$350 million; Britain, US$95
million; Sweden, US$75 million; and mainland China, US$65 million.

Yu, meanwhile, pointed out that Taiwan used to enjoy a vast
export market for its movies and music but is losing ground today,
with even the domestic market being dominated by imported work.

The Taiwan Historical and Cultural Map System contains basic maps
of Taiwan during the Portuguese, Spanish-colonial era; the era under
the occupation of warlord Cheng Cheng-kung during the Ming dynasty;
the era under Ching imperial governance; the Japanese-colonial era;
and the era after Taiwan was retroceded after 1945, said Fan.
